The paper discusses the reproducibility of scientific findings in machine learning, specifically in neural networks research. It also mentions a case study of reverse engineering DeepMind's Alpha Zero, which is a reinforcement learning algorithm used for playing games. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
